# Root .gitignore for the code-intelligence repo.
#
# The repo currently hosts two Go services under `services/`
# (`agent-memory/` and `clean-code/`); if/when other services land
# they should add their own toolchain-specific globs here.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Go toolchain output
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Test / coverage artifacts produced by `go test`.
*.test
*.out
coverage.txt
coverage.html
coverage.xml

# Profiles emitted by `go test -cpuprofile` / `-memprofile` etc.
*.prof
*.pprof
*.trace

# Vendored deps -- the service runs in module mode and pulls from
# the proxy; we never check `vendor/` into the repo.
vendor/

# Binaries built into the service tree by `go build` or by IDE
# debug sessions.
services/agent-memory/bin/
services/agent-memory/dist/
services/agent-memory/cmd/**/agent-memory
services/agent-memory/cmd/**/agent-memory.exe
services/agent-memory/cmd/**/*-linux
services/agent-memory/cmd/**/*-darwin
services/agent-memory/cmd/**/*-windows.exe
# Catch `go build ./cmd/<name>` invocations from the service
# root (which emit `services/agent-memory/<name>` /
# `services/agent-memory/<name>.exe` instead of landing under
# the cmd subdir).
services/agent-memory/*.exe
services/agent-memory/concept-promoter
services/agent-memory/consolidator
services/agent-memory/repoindexer
services/agent-memory/trace-log-pruner
services/agent-memory/span-ingestor

# clean-code service binaries (mirror of the agent-memory globs
# above). `make build` deposits the binary under bin/, which is
# the canonical build output. We deliberately do NOT ignore the
# extensionless name `clean-coded` under cmd/ because the gitignore
# pattern matcher cannot distinguish between a binary file named
# `clean-coded` (which we want to ignore) and the source directory
# `cmd/clean-coded/` (which we MUST track). The .exe / -linux /
# -darwin / -windows.exe suffixes below are extension-specific so
# they only match files, never the source directory. A developer
# who builds the binary in-place inside cmd/clean-coded/ should
# rely on `make clean` rather than gitignore.
services/clean-code/bin/
services/clean-code/dist/
services/clean-code/cmd/**/clean-coded.exe
services/clean-code/cmd/**/*-linux
services/clean-code/cmd/**/*-darwin
services/clean-code/cmd/**/*-windows.exe
services/clean-code/*.exe

# Go workspace files -- COMMITTED so the Forge per-iter test
# gate command `go test ./services/clean-code/test/conformance/...`
# (invoked from the repo root, not from inside a per-service
# module directory) can span the multi-module layout. The repo
# has 3 Go modules (root `github.com/microsoft/clean-code` plus
# `services/agent-memory` and `services/clean-code`) and a path
# spec that crosses module boundaries requires `go.work` to
# resolve. The previous "single module per service" comment
# pre-dated the from-repo-root gate requirement (Stage 10.3 iter
# 2 evaluator feedback item 1). `go.work.sum` is also committed
# per the upstream Go workspace convention.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Pre-commit / linter caches
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
.golangci-cache/
.pre-commit-cache/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Python toolchain output (services/agent-memory/cmd/reranker-sidecar/)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Bytecode caches emitted by `python` / `pytest` runs against
# the reranker-sidecar service. These appear next to every
# .py file but must never be tracked.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
# Virtualenv directories devs sometimes create alongside the
# reranker-sidecar to install requirements.txt locally.
.venv/
venv/
.python-version
# Pytest / coverage caches.
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / OS junk
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Local environment overrides
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
*.local.env

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Local-stack data dirs that should never be tracked. The
# `deploy/local/` compose file ships named docker volumes, but
# devs sometimes bind-mount instead -- the patterns below catch
# both common naming conventions.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
services/agent-memory/deploy/local/data/
services/agent-memory/deploy/local/**/_data/
services/clean-code/deploy/local/data/
services/clean-code/deploy/local/**/_data/

# claude
!.claude/
!CLAUDE.md

.worktree/
.forge/

# Forge plan-doc allowlist (auto-fix)
!/tests/

# Forge plan-doc allowlist (auto-fix)
!/tests/
